text:
Hey Jinafa, please meet Samantha your incredible E-Mentor we've been telling you about :smile:.  Feel free to introduce yourselves, say a little bit about what you would like to get out of the mentorship and continue chatting within this channel. :wave:

I will now be leaving the channel, but please direct message myself or emma-prospela if you have any questions. All the best for now! :slightly_smiling_face:

Hi Samantha, my names Jinafa and I am currently attending sixth form studying a-level biology,chemistry and psychology. My future aspirations include becoming a GP doctor so it would be really helpful if you could guide me! Thank you.

Hey Jinafa! So nice to meet you & I'm really excited to be your E-Mentor :smiley:
A little bit about me: I'm Samantha and I work at the NHS as part of the Royal Free NHS Hospital Trust (a group of 3 hospitals in London). Dexter sent me your profile which says your passionate about helping people and want to get into Medicine and I can certainly give you some guidance on that and insight to work life in the industry. How sure are you that you want to be a GP? To what extent have you considered other roles in the healthcare industry? Would be great to know so I know what to cover during our chats ;)
Also, your profile also says you're a professional henna artist which sounds fun. I love that you're slightly entrepreneurial too! Where do you do that? In my spare time I go to the gym a fair bit and cook lots!
Also anytime you want to send a message go ahead! I can't always reply straight away whilst at work but I will get back to you as soon as I can!

Wow that's pretty cool, so what kind of activities/roles does your job require you to do? Thanks, your guidance will mean a lot, I have been a bit lost recently and no I'm not certain I want to be a GP- I feel like many of the roles in the NHS aren't advertised as much as the others so I do lack knowledge in that topic and therefore I haven't really considered other roles. Ah thank you:smile: I usually do it twice a year in festivals such as eid when most people like to apply it. I can't cook:sob::sob: whenever I try I always either burn the food or burn myself:joy::joy: 


And no problem you can reply to me whenever you have time I do understand you're busy too, and I might be a bit late at replying too sometimes as I have sixth form so sorry in advance.

Also I have a question, hence I want to do medicine unis require/like students that have experience in the healthcare field, the only experience I got is 1 week at Charing Cross Hospital and at the moment I'm doing voluntary work at a care home. I am trying to get more work experience by emailing people but I am not having any luck. So I was also thinking to do volunteer work at King's college hospital for about 6 months? Do you think that would be too much as I have a-levels to study for too?
